messages.text: Hey guys, does anyone have any thoughts/ideas on the best way to return an array from running multiple queries on values in array rather than using a for loop? For example on the mountain page for the weather, I want to get the icons associated with their respective codes. I have an array [0,0,0,0,92,0] of the codes that I want to look up in the icons table to find their respective icon route, which would also be best returned in an array. The only ideas I have is a for loop, but then the results are inaccessible because the query results are in a .then function. No worries if you guys don’t have any thoughts on this, I’ll bring it to one of the instructors tomorrow!

I just wanted to provide a quick update on what I worked on today. There’s currently a pull request out! 

1. Created migrations and seed files for all of the tables
	- This may still need additional updating as we move foward and get a better understanding of all of the info we need
2. Created some user stories based on the wireframes 
3. Created the db/knex.js file and updated the knexfile.js so that it should be good to go for deployment when the time comes

I also had a few other thoughts on feautres when I was starting to go through the user stories:
- Ability to register/remove vehicle from a profile
	- When the user creates a ride, they could have the ability to select from a drop down menu the cars they have registered to their profile
- Nav Bar Additions
	- Messages, ride notifications (ride requests/ride cancelations)
- Ability to cancel an offered ride
- Ability to cancel from a ride joined
Hey Team! First of all, thanks <@U1W3R0RJ5> for putting those wireframes together! They look awesome.
